article.headline: Bradley 77, Drake 75
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Sam Maniscalco scored a career-high 23 points to lead Bradley past Drake 77-75 in double overtime in Missouri Valley play Saturday night. Theron Wilson scored 21 points and pulled down nine rebounds for Bradley (17-13, 10-8). Sam Singh came off the bench to chip in 13 points and eight rebounds, while Chris Roberts added 10 points and eight rebounds. Drake (17-14, 7-11) was up 29-28 at the half, but Bradley made up the difference in the second period, outscoring Drake 32-31. Both scored 12 points in the first overtime, but Bradley pulled away in the second, scoring 5 to Drake's 3. Josh Young scored 21 points for the Bulldogs and Josh Parker came off the bench to add 17. Brent Heemskerk had a double-double with 10 points and 10 rebounds. Drake shot 43.8 percent from the floor, while Bradley shot 39 percent.
